items.title: Israel Must Open Its Eyes
items.description: Defeating Hamas does not require starving a single child.

items.title: Earthquake Jolts New Jersey and New York City
items.description: The epicenter of the 3.0-magnitude quake, which struck around 10:20 p.m. on Saturday, was near Teterboro Airport in New Jersey.

items.title: David Rendall, Tenor Who Suffered Operatic Mishaps, Dies at 76
items.description: He appeared regularly at the Metropolitan Opera and sang in major European opera houses, but a stage accident in 2005 nearly ended his career.

items.title: No Passports, No Study Abroad: China Limits Public Employees’ Travel
items.description: Even low-level government employees like elementary school teachers and nurses have been ordered to hand in their passports, to enforce “discipline.”

items.title: With Festivities and Papal Prayer, the Vatican Aims to Attract the Young
items.description: At a gathering that has been called the “Catholic Woodstock,” the church has embraced influencers on social media as a way to engage the youth.
